10TH JULY 2026 
Day 3 Learning Summary – Advanced Python 

Studied advanced Python programming concepts and their practical applications. 
Learned the fundamentals of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP). 
Understood the concepts of Classes and Objects and how they are used to organize code. 
Explored Constructors (__init__) to initialize object attributes. 
Learned Inheritance to reuse code by creating child classes from parent classes. 
Studied Polymorphism and how methods can be overridden to provide different implementations. 
Gained an understanding of Encapsulation by restricting direct access to object data and Abstraction for hiding implementation details. 
Learned the basics of Iterators and Generators for efficient data traversal and generation. 
Explored Decorators to extend the functionality of functions without modifying their source code. 
Understood Context Managers and the use of the with statement for efficient resource management. 
Learned how to use the Logging module to record application events and debugging information. 
Studied JSON handling for reading from and writing data to JSON files. 
Explored REST API consumption using the requests library to retrieve data from web services. 
Developed a terminal-based Personal Expense Tracker mini project using Python. 
Implemented OOP concepts such as classes, objects, constructors, methods, loops, conditional statements, and user input while developing the project. 
Improved understanding of writing interactive Python applications and applying programming concepts through hands-on practice. 